<h2 class="m-4 font-medium text-xl">How it Works</h2>
<ul class="list-disc mb-8 mx-10">
  <li>Eleventy generates two static HTML files: The first is this "show" page. The second is an "edit" page.</li>
  <li>The two files are generated from the same Nunjucks template (turbo-frames-page.njk).</li>
  <li>The template has if/then conditions driven by a show/edit variable in the front matter of each of the two top-level templates.</li>
  <li>The main benefit is the fast, dynamic page behavior without writing any Javascript. The inline edits happen in about 50ms.</li>
  <li>Another benefits is that the HTML and styling for both pages comes from a single template, which makes it easier to keep both pages consistent, using multiple cursors when editing, for example.</li>
  <li>When a button is clicked, Turbo fetches the full show or edit page from the server, but only extracts the turbo-frame element it needs to update the page.</li>
</ul>
